<h2 id="s1">1. Test Environment &amp; Preconditions</h2>

<h3>1.1 Required Test Accounts</h3>
<table>
<tr><th>Account</th><th>Role</th><th>Purpose</th></tr>
<tr><td>Admin account</td><td><code>admin</code></td><td>Full access to all admin features</td></tr>
<tr><td>Support Admin account</td><td><code>support_admin</code></td><td>Test limited admin access</td></tr>
<tr><td>Auditor account</td><td><code>auditor</code></td><td>Test read-only admin access</td></tr>
<tr><td>Standard user account</td><td><code>user</code></td><td>Test regular user flows</td></tr>
<tr><td>Inactive/pending user</td><td><code>user</code> (inactive)</td><td>Test blocked access flow</td></tr>
<tr><td>Second firm user</td><td><code>user</code></td><td>Test firm-level isolation</td></tr>
</table>

<h3>1.2 Browsers to Test</h3>
<p class="check-item">☐ Chrome (latest) — Desktop &amp; Mobile</p>
<p class="check-item">☐ Safari (latest) — Desktop &amp; Mobile (iOS)</p>
<p class="check-item">☐ Firefox (latest) — Desktop</p>
<p class="check-item">☐ Edge (latest) — Desktop</p>

<h3>1.3 Preconditions</h3>
<p class="check-item">☐ Confirm all test accounts exist and can log in</p>
<p class="check-item">☐ Confirm at least one approved domain exists in the system</p>
<p class="check-item">☐ Confirm credits are available for the admin and standard user accounts</p>
<p class="check-item">☐ Prepare test documents: PDF searches, draft contracts, bank statements, payslips</p>

